{title: Chorus Recall}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Daylight breaks a[C]cross the [D]sky
[G]Birds are waking [C]up on [D]high
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[C]Sing it [G]loud, sing it [D]clear
[Em]Let the [C]whole wide [D]world [G]hear
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]Evening comes with [C]gentle [D]rain
[G]Washing clean the [C]window [D]pane
{end_of_verse}

{chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G]Midnight hums a [C]lulla[D]by
[G]Stars are spinning [C]way up [D]high
{end_of_verse}

{chorus}
